What really pissed me off is that when I told one of the passing nurses the pain was getting worse, she allowed me to know she was at lunch and had to wait for someone else to deal with me.

snippet.textDisplay: Misinformation on the Internet is dangerous, especially if it's about your health. I'm not a doctor yet, just a paramedic student very soon. A family friend asked if I recommend her to drink hydrogen peroxide because a Russian Ph.D. said it in a video that it treats many illnesses. I immediately told her not to, because if she does that, in about 48 hours post-exposure she can get into a coma and die. Of course, it depends on the dose and the type of chemical solution. NEVER believe to people who say things without strong scientifical evidence. Even if they are PhDs, a good physician ALWAYS TELLS YOU the negative benefits of a treatment EVEN IF THOSE ARE MILD. NEVER forget this. We bring so many people to the ER, and the problem is with this, is that it's easily preventable and it could have been prevented. If you want a treatment ALWAYS contact your doctor, and ask questions, they get their salary for it. Take care of yourselves, especially in America where healthcare isn't free. Don't feel sorry for your money, if you're sick, go to the doctor, your health should be the most important thing. Take care of yourself. - Paramedic Student from Hungary.

Hi Dr. Mike,
I love your channel (I love you to) and as I have a goal of becoming a doctor in future, this channel is very entertaining and also I gain a lot of knowledge.
I am Soumya. I am a 15 year old teenager and am from India. I want to become a gynecologist. I am in 9th grade and am working very hard. I have some questions and I request you to make a video on only the menstrual periods we have and some facts that we common people might not know. I am asking you these questions because even though nowadays everyone is quite open about these I never got proper answers to my question and am not being taken to doctor and also trusting google is dangerous. So my questions are:-
1. Why do the we have cramps, headache, acne, etc. during the period?
2. I recently had very severe breast pain, I asked my mom and she said it happens during the periods. Why? (Google said I had breast cancer, it freaked me out.)
3. Why do some girls like me have extremely severe period cramps and why do some girls don't have it at all?
4. My periods are extremely irregular (my periods started 3 years ago), but some of my friends already have regular periods. Why does it differ in everyone?
5. Should I consult a doctor because once I didn't had my period for 3 months and then I had my period 3 times in a single month. And I had drips of blood for the whole last month(I had period the whole last month) and now this month my period started properly. Is it normal?
6. Pads v/s Tampons v/s Menstrual cup? Which is the best? (I am a teenager so I obviously use a pad, but still..)
7. What is Birth control?
8. How to keep personal hygiene during the periods?
9. Why do we have a discharge when we are not on our periods?
10. Not related to periods: Please give tips to study and remember a lot information. I am an audio and visual learner but i am in school so i can't record what all is taught in school. So pls suggest what should I do. Also I am a night person. What are the advantages and disadvantages of being a day person or a night person.
I hope you will read my comment and answer my questions. It took me half an hour to write this. Hope you won't disappoint me. And also anyone who reads my comment pls do reply to it. Love your channel and pls do keep making such entertaining and educational videos. I won't say I have watched all of your videos but I have progressed a lot and I will watch each and every video of yours.
P.S.: I have taught my whole family how to do chest compressions by demonstrating on a teddy but it worked so I hope they will use it when in need.
With love :)
Soumya
